reply_text:
@underrated5210 Even in romantic black genre movies, more brown women are represented as romantic interest than lightkinned women. 

There are few all black blockbuster movies to begin with. But when there is a romantic interest, she's usually a brown woman. Robin Givens in the movie Boomerang, Whitney Houston and Kevin Costner in the movie Bodyguard, Chilli from TLC was Ushers love interest in his video for "you got it bad", in DMX movie "Belly", his love interest is very dark brown woman. In pro wrestling WCW and WWE Jacqueline Moore played the love interest for many men. I could list more. In the black movies on Tubi and BET, the love interest is usually a brown woman. Lightkinned Men and Women are a small percentage of the black race to begin with, and are even smaller in the black movie/film space. 

The reality is that this narrative that more LSW are casted in black movies, is simply not factual. It stirs up anger in misinformed people.
